PART 8: PRE-SUBMISSION CHECKLIST (Point-by-Point Verification)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Use this checklist before submitting. Each item maps directly to rubric requirements.

FORMAT REQUIREMENTS:
☐ Title present and specific to your argument
☐ Your name appears below the title
☐ Saved as .docx file

INTRODUCTION (15 points target):
☐ Paragraph has 4+ sentences (exceeds 3)
☐ Opens with engaging hook that captures interest
☐ Provides background/context introducing topic effectively
☐ Ends with thesis stating CLEAR POSITION
☐ Thesis previews your supporting reasons
☐ Smooth transition/connection to Body Paragraph 1

BODY PARAGRAPHS (15 points target):
☐ Exactly 3 body paragraphs (or more)
☐ Body ¶1 has 4+ sentences (exceeds 3)
☐ Body ¶2 has 4+ sentences (exceeds 3)
☐ Body ¶3 has 4+ sentences (exceeds 3)
☐ Each paragraph has ONE clear claim
☐ Each paragraph has detailed examples with specific evidence
☐ Each claim is supported with cited evidence
☐ Evidence is explained (not just dropped in)
☐ Effective transitions between paragraphs

ORGANIZATION (15 points target):
☐ Clear beginning (Introduction)
☐ Clear middle (Body paragraphs)
☐ Clear end (Conclusion)
☐ Ideas flow logically (each paragraph builds on previous)
☐ Strong, explicit transitions connect each segment
☐ No random tangents or off-topic content
☐ Paragraphs don't jump between unrelated ideas

IN-TEXT CITATIONS (15 points target):
☐ Every factual claim has a citation
☐ Body ¶1 has at least 1 citation
☐ Body ¶2 has at least 1 citation
☐ Body ¶3 has at least 1 citation
☐ All citations use correct MLA format
☐ Parenthetical citations are (Author) or (Organization)
☐ Citations appear BEFORE the period
☐ Direct quotes have quotation marks AND citations
☐ Paraphrases have citations (not just quotes)

CONCLUSION (15 points target):
☐ Paragraph has 4+ sentences (exceeds 3)
☐ Restates thesis in DIFFERENT words
☐ Summarizes ALL main points (all 3 body paragraph arguments)
☐ Provides thoughtful/reflective element
☐ Ends with memorable final thought
☐ NO new information, evidence, or arguments introduced

WORKS CITED (15 points target):
☐ On separate page (page break after conclusion)
☐ "Works Cited" centered at top (not bold, not underlined)
☐ Double-spaced throughout
☐ Entries alphabetized by first word
☐ Hanging indent format (first line flush left, subsequent indented)
☐ All sources from essay are listed
☐ All entries follow MLA 9 format exactly
☐ Each entry has: Author. "Title." Website, Publisher, Date, URL. Accessed Date.

MECHANICS (10 points target):
☐ No spelling errors
☐ No punctuation errors
☐ No grammar errors
☐ Varied sentence structures (mix of simple, compound, complex)
☐ Formal academic tone throughout
☐ No contractions (don't → do not)
☐ No first person (I, me, my, we)
☐ No second person (you, your)

