═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[YOUR TITLE - Specific to Your Argument]
[Your Name]

INTRODUCTION [Target: 4-6 sentences | Rubric: 15 points]
[Sentence 1-2: ENGAGING HOOK - statistic, question, scenario, or bold statement]
[Sentence 2-3: BACKGROUND/CONTEXT - explain the debate, name alternatives, establish stakes]
[Sentence 4: THESIS - clear position + preview of 3 reasons]
[Ensure SMOOTH CONNECTION to Body ¶1]

BODY PARAGRAPH 1 [Target: 5-7 sentences | Rubric: Part of 15 points]
[TOPIC SENTENCE - First claim, connects to thesis]
[EVIDENCE - Specific data with MLA citation]
[EXPLANATION - Why evidence supports claim]
[ADDITIONAL EVIDENCE or DEEPER ANALYSIS]
[LINK - Connect to thesis OR transition to next paragraph]

BODY PARAGRAPH 2 [Target: 5-7 sentences | Rubric: Part of 15 points]
[TOPIC SENTENCE with TRANSITION from ¶1]
[EVIDENCE with MLA citation]
[EXPLANATION]
[ADDITIONAL SUPPORT]
[LINK]

BODY PARAGRAPH 3: COUNTERARGUMENT [Target: 5-7 sentences | Rubric: Part of 15 points]
[ACKNOWLEDGE opposing view fairly: "While some argue..." / "Critics contend..."]
[PRESENT their strongest point]
[REBUTTAL with evidence and citation]
[EXPLAIN why your position remains stronger]
[LINK back to thesis]

CONCLUSION [Target: 4-6 sentences | Rubric: 15 points]
[RESTATE THESIS in different words - show what you've proven]
[SUMMARIZE ALL THREE main arguments in 1-2 sentences]
[THOUGHTFUL REFLECTION - broader meaning or nuanced acknowledgment]
[FINAL THOUGHT - memorable closing, implication, or call to action]
[NO new information]

Works Cited [Rubric: 15 points]

[Alphabetized entries in MLA 9 format with hanging indents]

