------------------|--------|-----------------------------------------------
Introduction      | 15     | 4+ sentences, engaging hook, clear thesis with position, smooth transition
Body Paragraphs   | 15     | 3+ paragraphs, 4+ sentences each, one claim per paragraph, detailed examples, transitions
Organization      | 15     | Highly organized, logical flow, strong explicit transitions
In-Text Citations | 15     | Every claim cited, proper MLA format throughout
Conclusion        | 15     | 4+ sentences, reinforces thesis, summarizes ALL points, no new details
Works Cited       | 15     | Correct formatting AND MLA citation (zero errors)
Mechanics         | 10     | Zero errors, varied sentence structures
------------------|--------|-----------------------------------------------
TOTAL             | 100    |

YOUR COMPETITIVE ADVANTAGE:

You have trade experience. This is rare and valuable for this topic. Use it:

1. In your counterargument paragraph, you can acknowledge trade benefits with AUTHENTICITY:
   "Having worked in the trades, the appeal of immediate income and hands-on work is understandable..."

2. Your rebuttal carries more weight because you're not arguing from ignorance:
   "However, the physical toll and career ceiling become apparent over time..."

3. This personal stake makes your argument for college more compelling:
   "Despite these firsthand experiences with trade work's advantages, the evidence for college remains overwhelming..."

Note: Even with this personal connection, maintain formal academic tone. Don't overuse first person—one brief acknowledgment of your experience is sufficient and powerful.

—End of Guide—
